Title: MAKEUP REVOLUTION SHOOK EYESHADOW PALETTE REVIEW + Trying Out New Products! | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! So in today's video I'm trying out the NEW Makeup Revolution Shook Eyeshadow Palette & then I wanted to try out some other products so I thought I'd throw them into this video as well! Hope you enjoy & thanks for watching! xoxo


UPDATE:

Makeup Revolution Shook Eyeshadow Palette - http://tidd.ly/ebc4d390
I've managed to use quite a few more colours and I still haven't changed my mind on this palette. Most of the mattes are chalky and the shimmers are very chunky with little pigmentation. You can create a pretty look with this palette but it's still not worth it with how difficult it is to work with.

LA Girl Pro Coverage Foundation in Fair - http://tidd.ly/5da801b3
I'm really liking this foundation and it surprised me because it does have decent staying power & it looks absolutely beautiful on camera!!

Ardell Faux Mink Demi Wispies - http://tidd.ly/b97cfb97
OBSESSED!!

Anastasia Beverly Hills x Amrezy Highlighter
Again I'm obsessed! Highly recommend if you can get your hands on it!

Colourpop All Star Setting Spray
I really like this setting spray, it does prolong the wear of my makeup so I'll definitely pick up the full size when this small one is finished!

Fenty Beauty Stunna Lip Paint in Unbutton - https://bit.ly/2XKrmxe
It's become my new go to nude! Formula is amazing, really comfortable and fades in a very flattering even way!

Title: Huda Beauty New Nude Eyeshadow Palette | First Impression Review & Tutorial | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! Today's video is all about the New Nude Eyeshadow Palette from Huda Beauty! If you have this palette please let me know what your thoughts are, & don't forget to let me know if they are any more products you would like me to review! Thanks for watching! xoxo


REVIEW UPDATE:
So I did manage to use the glitters and they were so much easier to use than I expected! They work well applied with either your fingers or brush - I was surprised how easy they were to use with a brush! I also used them with no base & with a glitter glue and the results were the same in terms of how the glitter looked on the eyelid. The only difference was there was quite a lot more fall out of the eye without glitter glue. The glitters definitely get a thumbs up from me!

Wet n Wild Mega Glo Contouring Palette in Dulce De Leche - Still love this, it feels so high end! Probably one of my favourite things I picked up!

Title: Fenty Beauty Pro Filt'r Soft Matte Foundation Shade 140 | First Impression Review | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! Today I'm finally reviewing the Fenty Beauty Pro Filt'r Soft Matte Foundation! Sorry it's taken me so long! I hope you find this video helpful & please let me know what other foundations you want me to review! Thanks for watching! xoxo

UPDATE:
The biggest thing I've learned with this foundation is that it is high mantience! If you find products that work well with it, it will look beautiful on the skin. But if the products you're using don't work with this foundation your skin will look a mess. 

I found that typical silicone primers don't work with this foundation, the foundation just doesn't sit well on top of them & can gather in places and look patchy. The best priming combination I found was using the Fenty Beauty Primer, then spraying my face with MAC Fix+ and applying the foundation whilst my skin is still a bit damp. 

Using a setting spray really helps! I don't get any oil coming through or fading if I use a setting spray. I'm still having the problem with this foundation not sitting right around my nose though! I haven't figured out a way to stop that happening! If you have any tips please let me know!

So overall, my opinion hasn't really changed. I neither love or hate this foundation - it's just okay. I will continue to use it but I would definitely advise getting a sample of this foundation first to test it out before you buy.

Title: Jouer Best Of Nudes Mini Lip Creme Set | Lip Swatches & Review | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! So I have another lip swatch video, really sorry if you're getting sick and tired of these. But today's review and lip swatches are on the Jouer Best Of Nudes Mini Lip Creme Set from the Jouer's Holiday 2017 collection. I really hope you enjoy this video and thanks for watching! xoxo


UPDATE:
As promised I did test out the formula of the Jouer liquid lipsticks. 

The formula is really long wearing, obviously the wear time will depend on eating/drinking but I found they lasted perfectly until I ate something. But a bonus was that there was minimal fading after eating so you can get away without reapplying. And I would recommend not reapplying because these liquid lipsticks do not layer well. They just feel really heavy and go slightly crumbly. However they are so easy to remove, all you need is some vaseline and tissue and they come right off. So even though it's more hassle it's better to remove the liquid lipstick completely and then reapply rather than apply another coat. But overall I really like these and they wear really comfortable to wear!

Title: Jaclyn Hill x Morphe Palette Review & Tutorial | IS IT WORTH THE HYPE? | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! I finally got round to filming my first impression review on the Jaclyn Hill & Morphe Palette! Let me know you thoughts on this palette & I hope you enjoy my review! Thanks for watching! xoxo

I filmed this about a week and a half ago so I have managed to try out most of the eyeshadows - it's mainly the bottom row I haven't tried, I'm sorry!! So from the ones I've tried I've only been disappointed by two which were the shades Twerk (one of the blue shades) and Faint (light shimmery pink). Twerk was just really hard to work and really hard to apply and blend, this shade is probably better for the lower lash line. And then Faint barely had any pigmentation which really confused me because it swatches really pretty, but once it's on the lid you can barely see it - and I used a brush/brush with Fix+ and my finger to apply the eyeshadow and I could just barely see anything. But the other shades are really good - even Silk Creme isn't as bad as I originally thought! I still have a few shades to try so I will keep you updated but overall I'm so impressed, it's definitely worth the hype and I love this palette!

Title: Morphe Liquid Lipsticks | Review, Lip Swatches & Wear Test | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! In today's video I'm testing out Morphe Liquid Lipsticks. I bought the shades Brunch, Suspect & Peanut and my update on Brunch & Suspect is further down. I hope this video was helpful and thanks for watching! xoxo


Please LIKE & SHARE this video! Don't forget to SUBSCRIBE!


5,000 SUBSCRIBER GIVEAWAY - https://youtu.be/v3MUkCZRHgE



OTHER PLACES TO FIND ME:
Instagram - https://instagram.com/daniellekirsty11


MORE LIQUID LIPSTICK REVIEWS:

Primark Liquid Lipsticks - https://youtu.be/WIWbez1GMb4

Ofra Liquid Lipsticks - https://youtu.be/g3N_kbOJtK0

Coloured Raine Liquid Lipsticks - https://youtu.be/LvSp4-UxdUc


UPDATE:

BRUNCH
My opinion hasn't changed on this shade. I would definitely give this shade a pass. I also noticed this shade was a lot more drying than the other two so if you suffer with dry lips or hate a drying liquid lipstick stay away from this one. The longer I wore this one the more unflattering it looked as well - it was literally sucking the life out of my lips and I couldn't wait to get it off. I also noticed the liquid lipstick started to break up/crumble on the inner part of my lips after only half an hour of wearing it. Overall I just think the formula on Brunch is disappointing in comparison to Suspect & Peanut. 

SUSPECT
I love this shade so much! I know I'm going to get a lot of use out of this one as soon as Autumn hits. It wore pretty much the same as Peanut. Lasted for around 7ish hours on the lips but did need reapplying after eating. It was comfortable and looked flattering on the lips.

Title: Testing Primark Liquid Lipsticks & Lip Liners | Lip Swatches & Review | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! So in today's video I'm putting Primark liquid lipsticks and lip liners to the test! I'm a huge fan of liquid lipsticks and these are the cheapest liquid lipsticks I've ever seen so I wanted to check them out. I also picked up some matching (even though they're not really matching, the caps on the lip liners are deceiving!) lip liners at my attempt at a Primark lip kit. I can't believe it but Primark have bought out their own lip kits! I'll probably pick those up at some point in the future. I hope you enjoyed this video and thanks for watching! xoxo

P.S. Please ignore my terrible makeup in this video, I've had some skin issues because of a certain product and my makeup just wasn't looking good. (I'll talk about what product it is in a future video). Also I don't know why my brows look like such a weird colour, I promise they didn't look like that in real life.

UPDATE:
So as promised I tested out the 3 liquid lipstick shades, not the lip liners, and here is what happened! A couple of things I missed in the video - all 3 colours are transfer proof and you get 7ml of product which is a huge amount for a liquid lipstick, so they really are amazing value for money!

KIM:
I have changed my mind slightly on the shade Kim because I was the most negative about this shade. I still don't like the colour on myself but that's just personal preference. My opinion has just slightly changed on the formula. It still feels the driest on the lips but trying it a second time it wasn't as streaky. I did shake and mix the product before applying it in the video but I must have just mixed it up a bit more the second time because it went on so much more opaque. I don't think you would need a lip liner underneath, so if you like the colour the formula's not as bad as I originally thought. Just make sure you shake it a lot before applying. This one is also the worst in terms of lasting power and fades a lot after eating and drinking. I would say it lasts for around 5-6 hours or it lasts until you eat or drink something. It layered completely fine but did become tacky with a second layer.

KENDALL:
For any cool tone lip lovers you need Kendall in your life! The colour is stunning, I know I'll get a lot of use out of this one because I think it's quite unique. The formula is better than Kim but it's still drying. Lasted for around 5-6 hours on the lips but did last better through eating and drinking than the shade Kim. But it does still fade in the centre of the lips so you will need to reapply. 

KARLA:
This is still my favourite out of all 3 and is going to be perfect for Autumn and Winter! For brown lip lovers this is the one for you. It performed very similar to Kendall, lasted for 5-6 hours, lasted better through eating and drinking but did still need to reapply because of fading in the centre of the lips.

Title: Colourpop Aquarius Bundle | Unboxing, Review & Lip Swatches | Beauty District
Description:
GET THEM HERE: https://bit.ly/34CMoSB
Use code DANIELLE for 10% off

Hey guys! I am so excited about today's video! This was the first time I'd ever tried anything from Colourpop! I've wanted to try Colourpop products for the longest time now, especially the lip products, (also the Super Shock Shadows and I'll be trying out those in a different video). Kathleen is one of my favourite YouTubers so obviously I wanted to support her and get the Aquarius bundle, and I also thought it was a good opportunity to try 3 lip formulas. Hope you enjoy and thanks for watching! xoxo 


UPDATE:

ULTRA GLOSSY LIP in Aquarius
I am absolutely in love with the ultra glossy lip and out of all three this is the one I've worn the most. I don't normally wear gloss so I'm not sure how long they usually last on the lips but this lasts around 2-3 hours, so you do need to re-apply a few times during the day. It also transfers very easily and completely comes off after eating.

ULTRA SATIN LIP in Aquarius
The ultra satin lip lasts so much longer than I was expecting! It lasts around 5-6 hours but it does transfer a bit so touch ups are needed after eating and drinking etc. It's a very comfortable formula to wear and non drying so I can completely understand why so many people love the satin lip formula.

ULTRA MATTE LIP in Aquarius 2
The ultra matte lip is obviously the longest lasting out of all three, it lasts around 8-9 hours. It doesn't last perfectly through eating but I was impressed with how well it did last, I only had to touch up the very center of my lips after eating. It is relatively transfer proof but it does start to transfer more easily the more layers you apply. It also gets tackier the more layers you apply. Like I said in the video it does feel drying but it didn't get any more drying throughout the day. Overall it's a good liquid lipstick and is definitely worth $5!

Title: Testing Ofra Liquid Lipsticks | First Impression Review & Wear Test | Beauty District
Description:
Hey guys! Today's video is another liquid lipstick first impressions and I'm testing out the Ofra Long Lasting Liquid Lipsticks! In the video I only did the wear test on the shade Manhattan, so check below for the update on the shade Bel Air. I hope you all found this helpful and please let me know what brand of liquid lipsticks you want me to try next! Thanks for watching! xoxo

UPDATE:

Both Manhattan and Bel Air have leaked! Manhattan leaked all over my drawer and over loads of other products which is very annoying. Luckily I managed to catch Bel Air in time before it leaked everywhere as well. I have to store them standing up now and I would never risk travelling with them. Let me know if this has happened to you because I may have just been really unlucky and received two faulty lipsticks. 

BEL AIR UPDATE:

The shade Bel Air actually lasted better through eating and drinking, there was also no feathering or bleeding. But it's not as flattering on the lips as Manhattan - lines on the lips are very obvious with Bel Air! I also noticed that Bel Air gathers in the middle of your lips and creates that horrible white rim on the inside of your lips which is not brilliant. I do love this shade though and it's been a nude shade I've reached for a lot.
